bility, dust structure, and/or star formation efficiency\nmay also be responsible for observed changes in the slope of the Tully-Fisher\nrelation, in the sharp increase in the thickness of dwarf galaxy disks, and in\nthe onset of bulges in galaxies with V_rot>120km/s. (Abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 19 Feb 2004 21:48:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
